The American Family Insurance All-USA performers of the week for Sept. 28-Oct. 3. Send any outstanding athletes for consideration for this list to sports@rgj.com. 
Jorden Carter, senior, Reed : Carter carried the ball 27 times for 113 yards in the Raiders 27-11 win over Reno on Friday. He was instrumental in sustaining drives for the Raiders. 
John York, junior, McQueen : York had 16 carries for 120 yds and 2 touchdowns in the Lancers 49-14 win over Hug on Friday. 
Korbin Marcum, junior, Spanish Springs: Marcum completed 17-of-25 passes for 248 yards and two scores in the Cougars 47-20 win over North Valleys on Friday. 
Julia Wenzel, senior, Bishop Manogue: Wenzel had 13 kills in the Miners’ 3-0 win over Galena on Tuesday volleyball and had 17 kills inthe Miners’ 3-1 win over Damonte Ranch on Thursday.
